Hosts France beat Germany 2-0 last night to reach the final of Euro 2016.Germany dominated the best part of first 45 minutes but failed to score and that came back to haunt them as France took the lead just before the break when Bastian Schweinsteiger handled the ball inside the box and Antoine Griezmann scored from resulting penalty to put homeside in the lead. France started better in second half and the eventually killed the tie when Griezmann scored his 2nd of the night and 6th overall in the tournament.It has taken France 58 years to defeat world champion Germany when it matters on the football pitch and, following a tumultuous evening in Marseille, they did it with a beaming smile on their face. 